'The way back was discovered?' Grieg says, all shocked like.<br>
<br>
'Yeah man a while ago, how long you been IN here?' Vinny says, still dealing out the cards. But Grieg just starts mumbling crazy like again, and then says 'The children laughed and threw garbage at me, when they forced me in here. I hate them.'<br>
<br>
'You gunna jabber or play cards?' Vinny said. And Grieg mumbles something else, and then turns over his card. It's a ten. Vinny is sitting to his left, so turns over HIS card, and its a 7. So Vinny asks him if he wants to Pain or Fear. Grieg says Pain, figuring his card is already higher, that he'll be able to get rid of Vinny's 7 no problem. They both roll, and Grieg roll a 1 and Vinny gets a 6. That's Vinny, luck of the halflings. So they total at Grieg with an 11 and Vinny with a 13, and Vinny shakes his head sadly and tells Grieg to bury his card. Greig is sorta pissed but goes to do it.<br>
<br>
When SUDDENLY, Randolf starts braying like a damned donkey and pointing at Grieg and laughing, going 'He can't play Pain/Fear! He sucks!' an all sorts of stupid crap. And Grieg's face is getting more and more purple, and I want to kick Randolf but I'm sitting so he just goes on and on.<br>
<br>
Well, Grieg floats up and looks at Randolf, and he's mad. 'What am I, here for your amusement?' he yells, but Randolf can't stop laughing. 'What am I a clown to you? I'm here to make you laugh?' He's angry as hells, but Randolf isn't getting it, and the rest of us get real quiet, not knowing what to do. And Grieg is fuming, 'You think this is funny, you stupid moron?' Grieg is going, and Randolf must finally figure it out, cause he stops giggling and starts staring at Grieg, who's circling him at this moment. And something must have frightened him, cause suddenly, his pants get this growing stain in the front, and he just lets go where he's standing, pissing himself. And Grieg looks at the stain and smiles, and then all the anger goes out of his voice. 'Yeah, that was sorta funny, me losing like that, huh?' he says all nice like, and starts to laugh. Well, we're all on edge, and Randolf starts to giggle with him, thinking its ok. And then Grieg laughs some more, and damned if it wasn't infectious, all of us start laughing, I mean tears from your eyes laughing, Grieg laughing the loudest of all, Randolf right along with him.<br>
<br>
And then suddenly Grieg stops laughing and grabs Randolfby the arm and opening that big weird mouth of his, takes a bite out of the kid's neck. <br>
<br>
Blood gushes everywhere and w're just sitting there in shock and Randolf is making these gurgling noises and Grieg is just biting away, at the kid's face, arms, taking out huge chunks. We're all getting drenched as randolf's getting eaten and before long he's nothing but a piles of bloody flesh and we're all in a daze and Moelle is staring real hard at the glowing rock thinking the same thing I'm thinking....no evac with that thing cancelling magic.<br>
<br>
'Let's play cards.' Grieg says suddenly, as if nothing happened, and floats down again.<br>
<br>
'Um, sure.' Vinny says, trying to be cool, but his hands are shaking. It's not every day you see someone get eaten, you know?<br>
<br>
'Hate kids.' Grieg said again. 'I'd kill them all if I could.' <br>
<br>
'That's cool, man.' Vinny says, playing a card on Dooma, who's not even watching, she's just looking at her dead cousin.<br>
<br>
'I could you know,' Grieg rambles, 'When I get out of here I'm going to talk to a few creatures I know, and kill all the kids. On Norrath, they are now?'<br>
<br>
'Yeah yeah.' Vinny says, trying to tune him out. 'Dooma, you going to play or what?' but Dooma's still staring at the bloody cousin.<br>
<br>
'How you going to kill them?' Moelle asks timidly. I haven't ever heard Moe timid, but we were all a little rattled.<br>
<br>
'Drown them.' Grieg said.<br>
<br>
'That's going to take some time.' I said, poking Dooma in the side so we could get the game done and find some way out of there. Dooma came out of her stare and made a bad play and Vinny took her card, but I don't think he cared if he won or lost at that point.<br>
<br>
'I'll get them all in one shot.' Grieg nodded. 'Shift the moon off its orbit, mass flooding on Norrath, earthquakes, the works... lock up the portals to Luclin...let them all drown...&quot;<br>
<br>
'How you going to move the moon?' I asked, intrigued despite the situation.<br>
<br>
'Rockets...' he whispered. 'With some help...'<br>
<br>
Well at the time, this was before the gnomes and all started talking about rockets and jet packs and stuff, so I didn't know what the hells he was talking about.<br>
<br>
'Cool.' I said, playing a card on Moelle. But Moelle, eyes wide listening to Grieg, had a brainstorm, thank Inny.<br>
<br>
She stood up. 'Me and Dooma have to powder our noses. Excuse us.' And she grabbed Dooma by the hand and practically dragged her up the stairs out of the room. Me and Vinny caught the idea.<br>
<br>
'Um, yeah...' Vinny said, 'I have to go drain the weasel, I'll be right back.' and up he goes after the girls, leaving me alone with the Purple Blob from Outer Space. <br>
<br>
Grieg's not paying much attention, instead, reaching for the other bottle of Black Poison and starts drinking it.<br>
<br>
'I'm gunna smoke, if you don't mind.' I said, and then made a show of patting my pockets. 'Damned, Vinny has my smokes, I'll be right back.' Grieg just nods and keeps drinking, and I get up and hurry out after them. Then minute i get out the door, Moelle starts chanting and we port the hell out.<br>
<br>
I have never been so damned happy to be out of somewhere. Dooma is freaking out, saying 'How I am I going to tell Uncle Dvinn his son is dead??' and I'm like 'Ambassador Dvinn is your uncle??!' and you think you know a chick and all...<br>
<br>
Well Vinny suggests we just STFU and pretend like Randolf never came out with us. And after a while, Dooma sees this is a good idea and we agree to never mention this again. And that was the end of our relationship with THOSE two chicks.<br>
<br>
But me and Vinny, well we never said a thing to nobody after that. Until, now that is.&quot;<br>
