&quot;Camille!&quot; Whizbang cried again. &quot;River, you cremated him yes? You burned the body?&quot;<br>
<br>
Camille was struck dumb by the question. But the frantic look in his eyes made her answer. &quot;Yes, Whiz, you were at the funeral. We spread the ashes in Kithicor River....&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Then what in hells...&quot; Whizbang said, as the machine once more increased the beeping. He started to pitch forward, and then pulled out of it. 'Then it wasn't him, or it was, but it wasn't...DAMMIT WOMAN GET ME OFF THIS MACHI...&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;GO TO BED!&quot; Pedi demanded, cold-cocking him across the chin, hard. Whizbang dropped like a stone back onto the bed, unconscious. The machine stopped making noises so frantically and settle to an even pitch. Pedi nursed her knuckles as she looked down at her husband. &quot;There, better.&quot; she said.<br>
<br>
&quot;Soooo,&quot; Talvarien said, inching slowly behind Rocsalt. &quot;If I join up with Walkers, this is the medical plan?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Nice right hook.&quot; Roc said, eyebrows raised, impressed.<br>
<br>
&quot;His chin is as hard as his head.&quot; Pedi said, &quot;It's his heart I'm worried about. And what in the world was he ranting about, about River and porting to the moon?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Something's going on up there.&quot; Camille said. &quot;It sounds like Whiz got caught in the middle of it.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;You know what he's talking about?&quot; Pedi said, fixing Camille with a look that demanded more.<br>
<br>
&quot;Yes, Pedi.&quot; Camille said. &quot;It's a long story. It's why I came...&quot;<br>
<br>
Then a knock at the door. Pedi hurried to answer, and came back in with Grelin.<br>
<br>
&quot;Message delivered.&quot; Grelin said.<br>
<br>
Suddenly Rocsalt burst out coughing again. Pedi grabbed him by the hand and dragged him from the room.<br>
<br>
&quot;Open your mouth.&quot; she ordered.<br>
<br>
&quot;It's ok, Pedi, just a thing I picked u...&quot; Roc began.<br>
<br>
&quot;OPEN YOUR MOUTH.&quot; she repeated.<br>
<br>
Rocsalt looked down at her, looking up at him from just below his belt, and decided the wisest thing to do was to comply. He crouched down in front of her and opened his mouth.<br>
<br>
&quot;Sorry, Roc, but no one goes near Whizbang with a possible cold.&quot; she said, drawing out a tongue depresser from her apron and applying it to his tongue.<br>
<br>
&quot;S hok.&quot; Roc said.<br>
<br>
&quot;This cough, flemmy?&quot; she asked, staring into his mouth.<br>
<br>
&quot;Nuh.&quot; he said.<br>
<br>
&quot;Swollen glands?&quot; <br>
<br>
&quot;Yuh.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Runny nose?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Nuh.&quot;<br>
<br>
She withdrew the depresser. &quot;Near the root of your tongue, your skin is turning yellow. I've never seen that before.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;I got a mouthful of spores from some shroom on the moon.&quot; Rocsalt explained. &quot;Yellow? Really?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Really.&quot; she said. &quot;It doesn't sound like a common cold, but when you're in there with Whiz, you wear this, from now on.&quot; She handed him a white gauze mask. He didn't argue with her; just tied it around his face covering his nose and mouth.<br>
<br>
&quot;Furthermore.&quot; she said, &quot;I want you to come back to see me tomorrow. I don't like the looks of this.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Yes ma'am.&quot; Rocsalt said dutifully.<br>
<br>
&quot;Pedi,&quot; Camille called from Whizbang's room. &quot;He's coming to.&quot;<br>
<br>
Pedi and Rocsalt hurried in to join them.<br>
